    "componentChoices": "The `appbar` component provides top-level navigation.  The `list-item` component, with its leading/trailing properties, is selected to display each setting. A `switch` component is used for toggle settings (e.g., Disable chats).  `textInput` is used for editable fields, while buttons handle actions.  The `dialog` component provides a modal to confirm destructive actions.   All components are selected from the design system for style consistency.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is achieved through clear section headings (using a larger `text` style), clear labels for each setting (using `Label/Medium` text style), and consistent spacing and padding.  The use of dividers between sections and neutral colors on backgrounds further enhances visual organization and readability. The primary color is used sparingly for key actions."
